The paper deals with mechanism design, which is a subfield of game theory (cs.GT). It also involves decision making under uncertainty, which is a common theme in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of Bayesian methods further supports the likelihood of cs.AI. The paper also involves optimization techniques, which can fall under machine learning (cs.LG) or data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the application of the work to crowdsourcing and online labor markets suggests a connection to economics and computation (cs.EC).
